Back to supply and demand

  • Demand shifts left and right in response to changes in income, population, tastes, etc

  • Demand moves along the demand curve in response to price changes.

  • Supply shifts in response to productivity changes or other factors that affect cost.

  • Supply moves along the supply curve in response to price changes.

  • economic rents - The value captured by suppliers or consumers when a market is not in equilibrium.

A supply shift

  • Explain why the bakeries would want to increase sales. Why can they not do so at the original price?
  • Describe how the actions of bakeries could adjust the industry to a new equilibrium.
  • What action might restaurants take while the market is not in equilibrium?
